 {"id":"bd-30d2.14","title":"Fix FeedbackCollector export/import decay timestamp frame drift","description":"Root-cause: feedback export stores last_signal_secs relative to collector Instant epoch, but import restores into a new collector epoch without rebasing. This can freeze decay/cleanup timing after restart or state transfer. Implement epoch-safe persistence semantics and regression tests proving decay behavior remains correct across export/import.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MaroonGlacier","created_at":"2026-02-16T06:34:48.917494869Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T06:44:06.411884845Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T06:44:06.411856892Z","close_reason":"Completed: fixed feedback export/import epoch drift, added regression tests, validated with rch check/clippy/tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-30d2.14","depends_on_id":"bd-30d2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T06:34:48.917494869Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-30d2.15","title":"Respect follow_symlinks=false for root directory symlinks in watcher snapshot","description":"Root cause: collect_snapshot_for_root() drops root symlink identity for directory symlinks, so traversal proceeds even when discovery.follow_symlinks is false. This can unexpectedly index symlinked trees and violate discovery policy. Fix root symlink handling and add regression tests for follow=false and follow=true behavior.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MaroonGlacier","created_at":"2026-02-16T06:44:18.128483303Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T06:49:01.316616958Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T06:49:01.316598744Z","close_reason":"Completed: root symlink follow-policy fix in watcher snapshot + unix regression tests + rch validation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-30d2.15","depends_on_id":"bd-30d2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T06:44:18.128483303Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-30d2.16","title":"Fix clippy float NaN guard in ranking priors constructor","description":"During bd-30d2.15 validation, cargo clippy for frankensearch-fsfs fails on PriorFamilyConfig::new using weight != weight NaN detection (clippy eq_op/float_cmp). Replace with const-safe is_nan logic and add/adjust regression coverage.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MaroonGlacier","created_at":"2026-02-16T06:46:41.430054756Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T06:49:04.318513222Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T06:49:04.318491231Z","close_reason":"Completed: replaced NaN self-comparison in PriorFamilyConfig::new with const-safe is_nan guard; rch test/check/clippy clean for fsfs lane","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-30d2.16","depends_on_id":"bd-30d2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T06:46:41.430054756Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
